      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is essential for modern justice because it acts as a bulwark against tyranny, protecting rights that the Founders may not have explicitly listed. It prevents the majority from trampling on the fundamental rights of minorities or individuals, ensuring that our legal system isn't just procedural but also morally just. This mechanism allows society to evolve and recognize new, vital liberties as the nation progresses, making it a dynamic tool for achieving true freedom.",
      "source": "target",
