    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I've heard some critics say that it's basically just \"judicial activism\" and that judges shouldn't be making up new rights that aren't written in the Constitution. How would you address those critics in my lesson? Would they have a valid point about the importance of staying strictly to the text?",
